This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it addresses the problem of person re-identification using deep convolutional neural networks. The paper also involves the use of a specially designed Pyramid Matching Module, which suggests that it could also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of multi-scale features, which could place it in the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. The use of deep learning techniques also suggests that it could belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the evaluation of the proposed approach against state-of-the-art methods, which could place it in the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
